<subSubSection id="4DBCDE2F908B7650D144500B969D623B" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" type="notes">
<paragraph id="E8460B46B7EBDD7AC6847D20AC20646B" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="19DB12E2D0B72A0B5DDA1CBDA244A0AB" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">
<bibRefCitation id="4541F034855B1999C714DB3C72787631" DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/3667210" author="Robyns, A" journalOrPublisher="Bulletin du Jardin botanique de l'Etat a Bruxelles" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" pagination="1 - 315" refId="B27" refString="Robyns, A, 1963. Essai de monographie du genre Bombax L. s.l. (Bombacaceae). Bulletin du Jardin botanique de l'Etat a Bruxelles 33: 1 - 315, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/3667210" title="Essai de monographie du genre Bombax L. s. l. (Bombacaceae)." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/3667210" volume="33" year="1963">Robyns (1963</bibRefCitation>
, p. 203) designated &quot;Riedel s.n. (LE)&quot; as lectotype of 
<taxonomicName id="C06B0456B2CA8A6710755D3A94AF2496" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bombacaceae" genus="Bombax" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bombax calophyllum" order="Malvales" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="calophyllum">
<emphasis id="83764A9AD0C8452B9CA6A1F5D8030012" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Bombax calophyllum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. When 
<bibRefCitation id="059EAB35D16D94DE0592EDE17AE886FE" DOI="https://doi.org/10.3989/ajbm.1998.v56.i2.235" author="Fernandez-Alonso, JL" journalOrPublisher="Anales del Jardin Botanico de Madrid" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" pagination="305 - 314" refId="B15" refString="Fernandez-Alonso, JL, 1998. Novedades taxonomicas, nomenclaturales y corologicas en el genero Pachira Aubl. (Bombacaceae). Anales del Jardin Botanico de Madrid 56: 305 - 314, DOI: https://doi.org/10.3989/ajbm.1998.v56.i2.235" title="Novedades taxonomicas, nomenclaturales y corologicas en el genero Pachira Aubl. (Bombacaceae)." url="https://doi.org/10.3989/ajbm.1998.v56.i2.235" volume="56" year="1998">
<normalizedToken id="8C1292E239E962F10B268F3965AE0601" originalValue="Fernández-Alonso">Fernandez-Alonso</normalizedToken>
(1998)
</bibRefCitation>
made the combination in 
<taxonomicName id="B82AD720D52BD09131D0E73CE5AF8F95" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bombacaceae" genus="Pachira" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pachira" order="Malvales" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4E240A735C58D5D069607B8DF1EF2037" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Pachira</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, he accepted 
<normalizedToken id="A8900421C31D82BBDD8E56D282FE7E9F" originalValue="Robyn’s">Robyn's</normalizedToken>
type designation, but stated that he had not seen the lectotype. Robyns annotated the two Riedel specimens in St. Petersburg (LE) cited above as &quot; 
<taxonomicName id="5A8524FECA70574ED6062C9545B3199A" authority="" authorityName="" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bombacaceae" genus="Bombacopsis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bombacopsis calophylla" order="Malvales" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" phylum="Magnoliophyta" rank="species" species="calophylla">
<emphasis id="29D3960E57115C9CC804D5902B6D46CB" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Bombacopsis calophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(K. Schum.) A. Robyns, 
<emphasis id="1CF284975ECC6F44423D53A128A12C8C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">comb. nov.</emphasis>
&quot; and wrote &quot; 
<emphasis id="A1C803BDD2C73F891F5AA411F560915B" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">lectotypus</emphasis>
&quot; on the one specimen that has a handwritten label indicating the type locality as &quot; 
<emphasis id="4D7F143E3B78FF07F201042998E11FA8" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Brasiliae</emphasis>
: 
<emphasis id="A29EE96E8E44B1C3FD47368413976373" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">R. Janeiro</emphasis>
,&quot; locality information that matches the protologue. The ICN (
<bibRefCitation id="F618B789FE0673C975DDC30B0F6D97A1" DOI="https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" author="Turland, NJ" journalOrPublisher="Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" refId="B40" refString="Turland, NJ, Wiersema, JH, Barrie, FR, Greuter, W, Hawksworth, DL, Herendeen, PS, Knapp, S, Kusber, W-H, Li, D-Z, Marhold, K, May, TW, McNeill, J, Monro, AM, Prado, J, Price, MJ, Smith, GF [Eds], 2018. International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashuetten. https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" title="International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashuetten." url="https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" year="2018">Turland et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
; Art. 7.10) requires that a type designation be effectively published and the mere annotation of a herbarium sheet does not meet this requirement. Our lectotypification (second step; see 
<bibRefCitation id="8492C3F8530033E315E0B1C1C11C72AD" DOI="https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" author="Turland, NJ" journalOrPublisher="Annals of the Missouri Botanical Garden" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" refId="B40" refString="Turland, NJ, Wiersema, JH, Barrie, FR, Greuter, W, Hawksworth, DL, Herendeen, PS, Knapp, S, Kusber, W-H, Li, D-Z, Marhold, K, May, TW, McNeill, J, Monro, AM, Prado, J, Price, MJ, Smith, GF [Eds], 2018. International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashuetten. https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" title="International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashuetten." url="https://doi.org/10.12705/Code.2018" year="2018">Turland et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
; Art. 9.17) narrows the type to a single element, a gathering that has loose leaves and a fragmented flower (calyx, ovary, and androecium). The isolectotype is sterile.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="40B316652393BAEFD8B7DC5FE86359F7" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">
The protologue of 
<taxonomicName id="72A70FB693495AA2420B2B98068C7BC3" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bombacaceae" genus="Bombax" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Bombax stenopodum" order="Malvales" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="stenopodum">
<emphasis id="8F19F2098AEAA7BD99AAD9CACF7CF85E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Bombax stenopodum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
cites a single collection, &quot;E. Ule n. 4631,&quot; which was deposited in Berlin (B†; see F neg. no. 9545). Inasmuch as the Berlin specimen was destroyed in WWII and no duplicate material has been found, we designate a neotype for this name. Our choice makes this name an obligate synonym of 
<taxonomicName id="DB415BE8C815D0305693535CCB78500A" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Bombacaceae" genus="Pachira" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Pachira calophylla" order="Malvales" pageId="0" pageNumber="53" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="calophylla">
<emphasis id="483B80B47C014825B229ED42ED865324" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="53">Pachira calophylla</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
